                  <interp inst="t17240415-11-crimeloc61" type="placeName" value="Queenhith"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17240415-11-crimeloc61" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17240415-11-off58 t17240415-11-crimeloc61"></join>, to be married by Mr. Lazenby the Minister of St. Anthony, and were so, and after they were married they went to the Dog-Tavern. That he being desir'd to take a Glass of Wine, went thither, and did observe the Prisoner to alter in his Countenance; and all that the Company could say, seem'd not to be enough to compose the Disorder that appear'd in him: So that he was ask'd if he repented of what he had done. But he answered, No. That they invited him to come in the Evening, and spend half an Hour with them; that he did go to them at an Alehouse near Sion College, and after some time, he saw them in Bed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17240415-11-person89">
